OL,3,CWelsh rugby boss warns it will take up
OL,4,Cto five years to be competitive again
OL,6,F"You have to at least consider
OL,7,Feverything."
OL,9,FBut Bradley went on to stress that the
OL,10,F"absolute plan" is for Wales to retain
OL,11,Ffour professional teams moving
OL,12,Fforward. He also pointed out that
OL,13,Fhaving the widest possible player pool
OL,14,Fto choose from would maximise Wales'
OL,15,Fchances of success at Test level.
OL,17,FAt times, it has felt like success at
OL,18,Fthe top level is all that has mattered
OL,19,Fto those holding the pursestrings in
OL,20,FWelsh rugby, and some feel it has led
OL,21,Fto a neglect of the regional game.
